comments: Booker (PHX) brings his off-arm toward Okogie's (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs as Booker slows his forward momentum.
Okogie (MIN) grabs and pulls Booker's (PHX) right arm after his gather.
Crowder (PHX) has his hand rested on Edwards' (MIN) right hip and marginal contact occurs before Crowder releases.
Ayton (PHX) places his arm against Rubio's (MIN) chest but does not extend it into him and dislodge him from his screening position.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Okogie's (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
Booker (PHX) and Okogie (MIN) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Rubio (MIN) passes the ball off of Bridges' (PHX) right leg as it is raised off of the floor and Bridges does not intentionally kick it.
Ayton (PHX) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Ayton (PHX) extends his hand into Towns' (MIN) front and initiates contact that impedes Towns' progress during the drive.
Saric (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Okogie's (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
Paul (PHX) goes to, not through, Okogie's (MIN) space and marginal contact occurs as Paul spins off of the contact.
Okogie (MIN) is moving laterally toward Booker (PHX) and marginal body contact occurs as Booker dribbles the ball off of Okogie's knee.
Okogie (MIN) is shuffling in a natural defensive position when his knee makes incidental contact with the ball during Booker's (PHX) dribble.
Crowder (PHX) commits a take foul on Hernangomez (MIN).
Saric (PHX) has a grasp of Towns' (MIN) left arm during rebounding and marginal contact occurs before Saric releases.
Towns (MIN) and Saric (PHX) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Saric (PHX) firms up on his left foot and absorbs the contact made with Okogie (MIN) as the screen is set, some of which occurs to Okogie's leg.
Towns (MIN) contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Booker's wrist after the release.
Crowder (PHX) initiates contact with his left hand across Edwards' (MIN) right arm after his gather, affecting the driving shot attempt.
Saric (PHX) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Edwards (MIN) engages with Crowder (PHX) and marginal contact occurs as Crowder moves freely through the lane during the inbound.
Rubio (MIN) commits a take foul on Saric (PHX).

Kaminsky (PHX) engages with Towns (MIN) along the baseline and marginal contact occurs to Towns' front prior to when he secures the rebound. MIN is awarded the timeout prior to any potential tie-up thereafter.
Booker (PHX) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Booker (PHX) initiates contact across Hernangomez's (MIN) right arm during the dunk attempt.

Crowder (PHX) has a grasp of Edwards' (MIN) jersey and quickly releases during rebounding. Crowder then swipes forward and marginal contact occurs with Edwards' arm and face as he attempts to dislodge the ball.  Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Edwards (MIN) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
